gene.long_name: solute carrier family 14 member 1 (Kidd blood group) (protein_coding)

annotation_set.note:
Polymorphisms in LRG_802, SLC14A1 give rise to antigenic variants of the Kidd blood group system, JK (ISBT 009). These LRG reference sequences represent the JK01/A allele (haplotype) of the Kidd blood group system.
Future ISBT tables will list LRG_802 t1, NM_001146036.2 (JK01/A) as the reference transcript/allele. Note that ISBT tables (1) have previously listed the JK02/B allele as the reference allele and NM_015865.6 as the reference transcript. However, this information was inconsistent in a number of ways.
NM_015865.5 (which represented JK02/b) was updated to NM_015865.6 (JK01/a) in order to match the primary reference genome assemblies (GRCh37/38, JK01/a).
Reference literature (1, 2) for blood group systems have listed NM_015865.6 as the reference transcript, but incorrectly described the model as an 11 exon model, with translation initiating in exon 4. NM_015865.6 is a 10 exon model, with translation initiating in exon 3. The current LRG t1 transcript, NM_001146036.2, is an 11 exon model, with translation initiating in exon 4.
NM_001146036.2 has the same coding sequence as NM_015865.6 (398 amino acids; NP_056949.4/NP_001139508.2/Q13336-1), and as such HGVS c-dot nomenclature and numbering can be directly lifted over from NM_015865.6 to NM_001146036.2.
--- References.
1) International Society for Blood Transfusion (ISBT) allele tables, JK (ISBT 009) v4.0 160705. http://www.isbtweb.org/working-parties/red-cell-immunogenetics-and-blood-group-terminology/ 2) The Blood Group Antigen FactsBook, 3rd Edition, Authors: Marion Reid, Christine Lomas-Francis, Martin Olsson
